se></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526241\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526241\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bui1665702903765.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bui1665702903765.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bui1665702903765.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bui1665702903765\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Procedural XML Handling\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bui1665702903765__procedural_xml_handling_121844\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Handling XML procedurally is much more flexible than Uniface's default approach. It enables you to write, read, and parse any XML data in streams and files. You can manipulate XML using Structs, or you can implement your own XML handler using the APIs provided by Uniface.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bui1665702903765__p_d38354e1_d38355e1_d38356e1\">For example, you can generate or read XML data required by non-Uniface sources such as web services; or perhaps you want to read or write an XML document that expresses entities as XML elements and fields as attributes; or extract and manipulate XML data that is embedded in fields.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bui1665702903765__p_d38357e1_d38358e1_d38359e1\">Uniface Struct functionality provides the most powerful way of transforming and manipulating XML. You can use <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svz1665702699008.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svz1665702699008.html\" title=\"Convert an XML document to a Struct.\">xmlToStruct</a>\n          and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kwk1665702698713.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kwk1665702698713.html\" title=\"Convert a Struct to XML, without a schema.\">structToXml</a>\n          ProcScript commands to convert and transform both XML and Uniface component structures. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kec1718082865771.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kec1718082865771.html\" title=\"A Struct is a tree-like data structure in memory that is used to dynamically manipulate complex data and transform it from or to XML, JSON, or Uniface component data. A Struct can be addressed by assigning it to a variable, parameter, or non-database field of type struct, and manipulated using ProcScript commands, access operators, and information functions. For information on using Structs, see Transforming Complex Data Using Structs.\">Structs</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qmy1665702567623.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qmy1665702567623.html\" title=\"You can dynamically transform complex data structures, such as XML, JSON, or Uniface component structures, into another format using in-memory data structures called Structs.\">Transforming Complex Data Using Structs</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bui1665702903765__p_d38360e1_d38361e1_d38362e1\">Alternatively, you can use Uniface component APIs to create your own SAX-like XML handler to write, read, and parse any XML data in streams and files:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bui1665702903765__li_d19421e1_d19422e1_d19423e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ccv1665702760000.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ccv1665702760000.html\" title=\"UXMLWRITER is an internal Uniface component that enables you to generate XML documents rather than having to code each character in the XML stream yourself.\">UXMLWRITER</a>—generate XML streams.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bui1665702903765__li_d19424e1_d19425e1_d19426e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hni1665702758666.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hni1665702758666.html\" title=\"UXMLREADER is an internal Uniface component that enables you to parse XML documents stored in files, fields, or variables.\">UXMLREADER</a> —read XML data from a data stream or file.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bui1665702903765__li_d19427e1_d19428e1_d19429e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqh1665702758875.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqh1665702758875.html\" title=\"SAX callback operations are APIs that can be implemented on a user-defined SAX event handler. They enable you to use the parser information to manipulate and analyze XML data, and handle any errors that may be encountered.\">SAX Callback Operations</a>—define a SAX\n            callback handler that implements these operations to process callbacks from the XML\n            parser executed by UXMLREADER. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bui1665702903765__p_d38363e1_d38364e1_d38365e1\">In addition, there is a component API for XML transformations—\n         <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qlu1665702769393.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qlu1665702769393.html\" title=\"USYSXSLT is a Uniface component that provides services for transforming XML streams at runtime using XSLT stylesheets.\">USYSXSLT</a>. However, this API does not support transformations to non-XML formats.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526241\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526241\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Procedural XML Handling Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Procedural XML Handling Handling XML procedurally is much more flexible than Uniface's default approach. It enables you to write, read, and parse any XML data in streams and files. You can manipulate XML using Structs, or you can implement your own XML handler using the APIs provided by Uniface. For example, you can generate or read XML data required by non-Uniface sources such as web services; or perhaps you want to read or write an XML document that expresses entities as XML elements and fields as attributes; or extract and manipulate XML data that is embedded in fields. Uniface Struct functionality provides the most powerful way of transforming and manipulating XML. You can use xmlToStruct and structToXml ProcScript commands to convert and transform both XML and Uniface component structures. For more information, see Structs and Transforming Complex Data Using Structs . Alternatively, you can use Uniface component APIs to create your own SAX-like XML handler to write, read, and parse any XML data in streams and files: UXMLWRITER —generate XML streams. UXMLREADER —read XML data from a data stream or file. SAX Callback Operations —define a SAX callback handler that implements these operations to process callbacks from the XML parser executed by UXMLREADER. In addition, there is a component API for XML transformations— USYSXSLT . However, this API does not support transformations to non-XML formats. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}